 to shape her own opportunities. During these two decades, each woman enjoyed expanding visibility due to an increasingly global mass culture, rising nationalism in Asia, the emergence of the United States from the shadows of imperialism to world power, and the more assertive participation of women in civic and consumer culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aInternational relations. 7aHISTORY / United States / General.2bisacsh  a20th century.  aamerica.  aamerican culture.  aamerican history.  aamerican perspective.  aanna may wong.  aanthropology.  aasian nationalism.  achina.  achinese americans.  aconsumer culture.  ademographics.  aethnographers.  agender issues.  aglobalism.  aglobalization.  ahistorians.  ahistory of orientalism.  ainternational relations.  amass culture.  amayling soong.  amodern history.  anonfiction study.  aorientalism.  aothering.  apearl s buck.  atransnationalism.  aunited states.  awomen in america.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052024422140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093863240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520938632423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520938632/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY